The evolution of the Bulgarian real estate market is spectacular, the attention of all Europe has been turned towards this Balkan country in the past.
What, or who bought on this EU market which is always the cheapest but who will quickly become expensive?
Analysis of the Bulgarian division of Re/Max.
Currently, in real estate, Bulgaria is undoubtedly the most vogue target in Eastern Europe with its ski apartments and houses on the cheap seaside.
In the mountains, the most popular regions are Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitosa and, on the shore, Albena, the "Golden Sails", the "Côte du Sole", the former Sozopol and Nessebar but they are increasingly looking for a building in the Kavarna region and Balcik as well.
